<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11049f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11049f">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11049f"> 49(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> snobsis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mais qui sont ces gens &ldquo;distingu&eacute;s&rdquo;? Des Hutins! puis des demi-lettr&eacute;s de toutes sortes, fiers de faire para&icirc;tre ainsi quelle est la qualit&eacute; de leur culture; mais surtout des snobs: ceux-l&agrave; m&ecirc;mes qui ne manquent jamais de prononcer avec &ldquo;le plus pur accent britannique&rdquo; <i>square</i>, <i>rail</i>, <i>clown</i>, <i>football association</i>, <i>cross country</i>, <i>rallye paper</i> ou <i>garden party</i>, au lieu de dire ces mots comme on les entend commun&eacute;ment: squ&acirc;re, raille, cloune, foutebolle association, etc. Pr&eacute;tention enfin, Pr&eacute;tention et P&eacute;danterie! <font color="green">[But who are these &ldquo;distinguished&rdquo; people? The Joneses! Then the half-literate of all kinds, proud to pretend that they have a culture of some sort; but most of all the <mark>snobs</mark>: those who never fail to pronounce with &ldquo;the purest British accent&rdquo; the words <i>square</i>, <i>rail</i>, <i>clown</i>, <i>football association</i>, <i>cross country</i>, <i>rallye paper</i> or <i>garden party</i>, instead of pronouncing these words as one often hears them: squ&acirc;re, raille, cloune, foutebolle association, etc. Pretention in other words, Pretention and Pedantry!]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger et Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="JBAT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JBAT"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 91</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
